  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "BSW functional clusters are groups of functionally coherent BSW modules"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Types of Clusters"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Communication Clusters",
        "Memory Cluster",
        "I/O Cluster",
        "Watchdog Cluster"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Guidelines for BSW Clusters"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The same functional cluster can only exist at most once per BSW partition."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The communication and synchronization between modules in BSW functional clusters of the same type is not standardized"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "It will be implemented by communication between entities (e.g. by a master and satellites) of specific modules, which can use non-standardized interfaces for communication across BSW partition boundaries"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "BSW Split requires"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Thorough analysis of the considered modules",
        "Deep knowledge of BSW stack and its internal interactions and sequences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Vector Microsar provides"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Pre defined set of modules for relocation",
        "Additional functionality to support relocation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below module have satellite implementation from Vector"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "WdgM and WdgIf",
        "Dem",
        "EcuM",
        "Det"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below module have Proxy implementation from Vector"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Com",
        "NvM"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Communication Cluster"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Relocation of individual channel is not possible in communication cluster"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Example of communication cluster, Where all Ethernet related Stack can be mapped to Core1, like TCP/IP, SoAd, EthSM, Switch driver"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/06_Autosar%20-%20BSW%20Split%20Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-42-39.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/06_Autosar - BSW Split Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-42-39.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "COM stack uses proxy implementation to handle signals from other core"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/06_Autosar%20-%20BSW%20Split%20Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-51-45.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/06_Autosar - BSW Split Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-51-45.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PduR acts as a router between cores for"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Interface PDUs",
        "Transport protocol PDUs"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/06_Autosar%20-%20BSW%20Split%20Architecture/image2022-8-19_14-3-58.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/06_Autosar - BSW Split Architecture/image2022-8-19_14-3-58.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Watchdog Cluster"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There are 2 different concepts on how the WdgM Stack can react to detected violations, the independent and combined core reaction concept"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Independent Core reaction"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/06_Autosar%20-%20BSW%20Split%20Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-47-47.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/06_Autosar - BSW Split Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-47-47.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Combined core reaction"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/06_Autosar%20-%20BSW%20Split%20Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-48-49.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/06_Autosar - BSW Split Architecture/image2022-8-19_13-48-49.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Memory Cluster"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Vector supports Nvm-Proxy component to support multicore NVM handling"
    }
  ],
